<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="situation-n">situation <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /ˌsɪtʃu'eɪʃn/    美 /ˌsɪtʃu'eɪʃn/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>处境；形势：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s helpful to put children in a <strong>situation where</strong> they can see themselves differently.
让孩子置身于能让他们看到不一样的自己的局面里，这对他们是有帮助的。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When you are <strong>in a</strong> tight <strong>situation</strong>, don’t panic.
当你身处险境时，不要惊慌。</p><footer>2010 江西</footer></div>

<h4 id="2-location">2.<strong>[正式用语] 位置；地点 (location)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>choose a situation for a camp
选扎营地</p></div>

